metadata.name: To the Light
metadata.description:
From my recent film "Dreamers", early morning over Parkville, Missouri. Down below is the mighty Missouri River, also known as the big muddy. This was a fleeting view of the river fog on a very cold fall morning. It was constantly changing as the fog boiled off. I just happened to be there at a perfect time.

About the photographer -

Jim Jamieson is an accomplished Midwest nature and wildlife photographer, publisher, avid kayaker and owner of ImageStream Press. Jim has been a photographer since 1997 and has four publications Bosque del Apache National Wildlife Refuge: 48 Hours of Flight, Our National Parks and Wildlife Refuges: Capturing the Rhythms of Light and Land, The Flight Deck: Digital Rhythms of Our National Wildlife Refuges and Minnesota: Chasing the Seasons from the North Shore to the Mississippi.

His books have received a number of prestigious national awards and favorable reviews. His work has also been featured in national publications such as Outdoor Photographer, PHOTO
